 **Shared Analysis** (Step 1), since we're analyzing CI artifacts, not running tests locally.\\n    30→\\n    31→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    32→\\n    33→## Step L2: First Run\\n    34→\\n    35→```bash\\n    36→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    37→```\\n    38→\\n    39→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    40→\\n    41→## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    42→\\n    43→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    44→\\n    45→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    46→\\n    47→## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    48→\\n    49→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    50→\\n    51→## Step L5: Collect Results\\n    52→\\n    53→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    54→\\n    55→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    56→\\n    57→---\\n    58→\\n    59→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n    60→\\n    61→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n    62→\\n    63→For each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n    64→- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n    65→- What was expected (from test source)\\n    66→- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n    67→- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n    68→\\n    69→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n    70→\\n    71→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n    72→\\n    73→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n    74→\\n    75→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n    76→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n    77→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n    78→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n    79→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    80→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    81→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n    82→\\n    83→**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n    84→- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n    85→- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n    86→\\n    87→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n    88→\\n    89→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n    90→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n    91→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n    92→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n    93→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n    94→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n    95→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n    96→\\n    97→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n    98→\\n    99→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n   100→\\n   101→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n   102→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n   103→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n   104→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   105→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   106→- Agent produced no output\\n   107→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   108→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   109→\\n   110→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n   111→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   112→- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n   113→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   114→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   115→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   116→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   117→\\n   118→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   119→\\n   120→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   121→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   122→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   123→\\n   124→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   125→\\n   126→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   127→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   128→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   129→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   130→\\n   131→### Step 4: Take Action\\n   132→\\n   133→Present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n   134→\\n   135→#### Present Findings Report\\n   136→\\n   137→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   138→\\n   139→```\\n   140→## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n   141→\\n   142→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   143→**Evidence:**\\n   144→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   145→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   146→```\\n   147→\\n   148→#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n   149→\\n   150→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n   151→\\n   152→```\\n   153→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   154→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   155→  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n   156→```\\n   157→\\n   158→Common flaky fixes:\\n   159→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   160→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   161→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   162→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   163→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   164→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   165→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   166→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   167→\\n   168→#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n   169→\\n   170→```\\n   171→**Root cause analysis:**\\n   172→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   173→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n   174→  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n   175→  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n   176→```\\n   177→\\n   178→#### Ask the user\\n   179→\\n   180→Prompt the user:\\n   181→\\n   182→> **Should I fix these?**\\n   183→> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n   184→> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n   185→\\n   186→Wait for user response before proceeding.\\n   187→\\n   188→#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n   189→\\n   190→For **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n   191→1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   192→2. Run verification:\\n   193→   ```bash\\n   194→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   195→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   196→   ```\\n   197→3. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n   198→\\n   199→For **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n   200→1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   201→2. Run relevant tests to verify:\\n   202→   ```bash\\n   203→   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   204→   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   205→   ```\\n   206→3. Report results to the user.\\n   207→\\n   208→### Step 5: Summary\\n   209→\\n   210→Print a summary table:\\n   211→```\\n   212→| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action Taken |\\n   213→|------|----------|---------|---------------|-------------|\\n   214→| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | Fixed in working tree |\\n   215→| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Fix applied, tests passing |\\n   216→| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | Skipped (user declined) |\\n   217→```\\n   218→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"a7899498-0325-448f-9597-1924db64144a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:40:44.533Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md\",\"content\":\"---\\nname: e2e-triage\\ndescription: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise, classify flaky vs real bug. Presents findings and applies fixes in-place.\\n---\\n\\n# E2E Triage\\n\\nTriage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Analyzes artifacts and re-runs failing tests locally to distinguish flaky from real bugs. Presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step L1: Parse User Input\\n\\nThe user provides one or more of:\\n- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n- **CI run reference** — triggers artifact download instead of local re-runs:\\n  - `latest CI run` / `latest` — most recent failed E2E run on main\\n  - A GitHub Actions run ID (numeric, e.g., `12345678`)\\n  - A GitHub Actions run URL\\n\\n**CI artifact download:** When a CI run reference is provided, download artifacts using:\\n\\n```bash\\nscripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <latest | RUN_ID | RUN_URL>\\n```\\n\\nThe script outputs the absolute artifact path as its **last line of stdout** — capture that and use it as the artifact path for analysis. After downloading, **skip Steps L2–L5** (local re-runs) and go straight to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1), since we're analyzing CI artifacts, not running tests locally.\\n\\n**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n\\n## Step L2: First Run\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n```\\n\\nCapture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n\\n## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n\\nIf the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n\\nIf the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n\\n## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n\\nIf results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n\\n## Step L5: Collect Results\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n\\nProceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n\\n### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n\\nFor each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive